From: Andreas Gruenbacher <agruen@suse.de>
Subject: SUSE/external support flag in modules
Patch-mainline: Never, SLES feature
References: bsc#148091 bsc#974406 jsc#PED-5759

Add an ability for SLE kernels to distinguish modules as supported,
externally supported or unsupported.

The feature consists of several parts:
* Add an option to modpost to record the "supported" level for a given
  module and update the build logic to read this information from
  Module.supported.
* Extend the kernel to parse the "supported" level upon a module load.
  Record it per module to allow its display when information about the
  module is being printed and aggregate the levels in taint flags for
  a quick overview of the entire system.
* Introduce the "unsupported" kernel parameter which controls whether
  unsupported modules can be loaded.

During the runtime, supportability level of each module is exposed in
file /sys/module/<module>/supported and the aggregated status for the
entire system is available in /sys/kernel/supported. Loading an
"unsupported" module also directly taints the kernel and appears in
/proc/sys/kernel/tainted.

Note: function get_next_line() was removed by mainline commit
75893572d453 ("modpost: remove get_next_text() and make
{grab,release_}file static"), restore it.

